"<method name=\"is_hmd_feature_supported\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"feature\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether the connected glasses support a [code]FEATURE_*[/code] capability ([code]IsHMDFeatureSupported[/code]). [code]false[/code] when unavailable. This is the device-accurate gate the SDK itself uses.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"is_camera_supported\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether the connected glasses have an RGB camera ([code]IsHMDFeatureSupported(FEATURE_RGB_CAMERA)[/code]). The Air 2 Ultra reports [code]false[/code] — gate the camera on this so it is never opened there.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_device_resolution\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Vector2i\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"component\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  A [code]COMPONENT_*[/code] device&#39;s pixel resolution ([code]Vector2i.ZERO[/code] when unavailable).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_camera_intrinsics\">\n"
"  <return type=\"PackedFloat32Array\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"component\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  A [code]COMPONENT_*[/code] camera&#39;s intrinsics as [code][fx, fy, cx, cy][/code] in pixels (empty when unavailable).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_device_pose_from_head\">\n"
"  <return type=\"PackedFloat32Array\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"component\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  A [code]COMPONENT_*[/code] device&#39;s extrinsic relative to Head as a raw Unity [code]Pose[/code]: [code][pos x,y,z, quat x,y,z,w][/code] (Unity left-handed — convert to Godot; see coordinate-systems-notes). Empty when unavailable.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_camera_projection_matrix\">\n"
"  <return type=\"PackedFloat32Array\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"component\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"1\" name=\"near\" type=\"float\" /><param index=\"2\" name=\"far\" type=\"float\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  A [code]COMPONENT_*[/code] camera&#39;s 4x4 projection matrix (16 floats, Unity column-major) for [code][near, far][/code]. Empty when unavailable.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"is_plane_detection_available\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether the connected glasses support plane detection. Gated by [[code]Self::is_ar_perception_available[/code]] (6DoF + no RGB camera = the Air 2 Ultra). [code]false[/code] until the session is up, so query it at toggle time, not at startup.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_plane_detection_mode\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"mode\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Enable plane detection ([code]PLANE_HORIZONTAL | PLANE_VERTICAL[/code] flags). Needs a live 6DoF session; returns the SDK bool (false when unavailable). Call after [code]is_session_started()[/code].\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_plane_detection_mode\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Current [code]PlaneDetectionMode[/code] flags, or [code]-1[/code] when unavailable.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"poll_planes\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Dictionary\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Poll detected-plane changes since the last call. Returns [code]{ &quot;added&quot;: Array, &quot;updated&quot;: Array, &quot;removed&quot;: Array }[/code] where each added/updated entry is a [code]Dictionary { id: String, transform: Transform3D, center: Vector2, size: Vector2, alignment: int }[/code] and [code]removed[/code] is an array of id strings. Call once per frame (drives the SDK&#39;s change queue).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_plane_boundary\">\n"
"  <return type=\"PackedVector2Array\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"id\" type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Boundary polygon (plane-local points) of a detected plane, by its id string from [code]poll_planes[/code].\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"is_anchor_available\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether the connected glasses support spatial anchors. Gated by [[code]Self::is_ar_perception_available[/code]] (6DoF + no RGB camera = the Air 2 Ultra). [code]false[/code] until the session is up.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_anchor_enabled\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"enabled\" type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Enable/disable the anchor subsystem (call once before acquiring). Returns whether the export was present. Needs a live 6DoF session for anchors to actually track.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_anchor_mapping_dir\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"dir\" type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Point the anchor subsystem at a writable directory for its saved-anchor map files (e.g. [code]OS.get_user_data_dir()[/code]). Call before saving/loading.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"acquire_anchor\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Dictionary\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"pose\" type=\"Transform3D\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Create a new anchor at [code]pose[/code] (a world [code]Transform3D[/code]). Returns the anchor [code]Dictionary[/code] ([code]{ id, transform, tracking_state, session_id }[/code]) or an empty dict on failure.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"poll_anchors\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Dictionary\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Poll anchor changes since the last call: [code]{ &quot;added&quot;: Array, &quot;updated&quot;: Array, &quot;removed&quot;: Array }[/code] (each added/updated entry a [code]Dictionary { id, transform, tracking_state, session_id }[/code]; [code]removed[/code] an array of id strings). Call once per frame to drive the SDK&#39;s change queue.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"save_anchor\">\n"
"  <return type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"id\" type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Persist an anchor (by its id from [code]poll_anchors[/code]) and return its [code]Guid[/code] key as a 32-hex string (empty on failure). Estimate quality ≥ SUFFICIENT first; enumerate saved keys yourself.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"load_anchor\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Dictionary\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"guid\" type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Restore a saved anchor by its [code]Guid[/code] string. Returns the anchor [code]Dictionary[/code] or an empty dict.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"remove_anchor\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"id\" type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Drop a tracked anchor by its id. Returns the SDK bool (or [code]false[/code] when unavailable).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"remap_anchor\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"id\" type=\"String\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Re-localize an anchor into the current map. Returns the SDK bool (or [code]false[/code] when unavailable).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"estimate_anchor_quality\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"id\" type=\"String\" /><param index=\"1\" name=\"pose\" type=\"Transform3D\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Estimate an anchor&#39;s save quality ([code]ANCHOR_QUALITY_*[/code]) at [code]pose[/code], or [code]-1[/code] on failure.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"is_image_tracking_available\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether the connected glasses support image tracking. Gated by [[code]Self::is_ar_perception_available[/code]] (6DoF + no RGB camera = the Air 2 Ultra). [code]false[/code] until the session is up.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"init_image_database\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"blob\" type=\"PackedByteArray\" /><param index=\"1\" name=\"image_guids\" type=\"PackedStringArray\" /><param index=\"2\" name=\"image_sizes\" type=\"PackedVector2Array\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Build a tracking database from a reference-image DB [code]blob[/code] (produced by [code]trackableImageTools[/code]) plus, per image, its baked [code]image_guids[/code] (32-hex, aligned with [code]image_sizes[/code]) and physical [code]image_sizes[/code] (metres). Returns the DB handle ([code]0[/code] on failure). Pass it to [[code]Self::set_image_database[/code]] to activate, and keep it for [[code]Self::release_image_database[/code]].\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_image_database\">\n"
"  <return type=\"void\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"handle\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Activate a database from [[code]Self::init_image_database[/code]] (pass [code]0[/code] to disable image tracking).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"image_reference_count\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"handle\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Number of reference images in a database, or [code]0[/code] when unavailable.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"release_image_database\">\n"
"  <return type=\"void\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"handle\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Free a database from [[code]Self::init_image_database[/code]].\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"poll_images\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Dictionary\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Poll tracked-image changes since the last call: [code]{ &quot;added&quot;: Array, &quot;updated&quot;: Array,\n"
" &quot;removed&quot;: Array }[/code] (each added/updated entry a [code]Dictionary { id, source_image, transform,\n"
" size, tracking_state }[/code]; [code]removed[/code] an array of id strings). Call once per frame.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"is_meshing_supported\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether the connected glasses support depth meshing. Gated by [[code]Self::is_ar_perception_available[/code]] (6DoF + no RGB camera = the Air 2 Ultra). [code]false[/code] until the session is up.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_meshing_enabled\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"on\" type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Enable/disable depth meshing ([code]NativePerception::SetMeshingEnabled[/code]). Returns whether the call reached the SDK (perception up); poll [code]poll_mesh_blocks[/code] after enabling.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"poll_mesh_blocks\">\n"
"  <return type=\"Array\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Poll the current mesh blocks. Returns an [code]Array[/code] of [code]Dictionary { id: String, state: int,\n"
" vertices: PackedVector3Array, normals: PackedVector3Array, indices: PackedInt32Array }[/code]. [code]state == 2[/code] means the block was removed; build/update an [code]ArrayMesh[/code] per block otherwise.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"stream_start\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"output\" type=\"String\" /><param index=\"1\" name=\"width\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"2\" name=\"height\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"3\" name=\"bitrate\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"4\" name=\"fps\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"5\" name=\"with_mic\" type=\"bool\" /><param index=\"6\" name=\"with_internal_audio\" type=\"bool\" /><param index=\"7\" name=\"with_alpha\" type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Start streaming the FPV to [code]output[/code] — an [code]rtp://ip:port[/code] / [code]rtmp://…[/code] URL or a local file path (the URL scheme picks local/RTMP/RTP). Returns whether the encoder started. Then feed the view&#39;s GL texture each frame via [[code]Self::stream_push_frame[/code]] from a [code]RenderingServer.call_on_render_thread[/code].\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"stream_push_audio\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"samples\" type=\"PackedByteArray\" /><param index=\"1\" name=\"n_samples\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"2\" name=\"bytes_per_sample\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"3\" name=\"channels\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"4\" name=\"sample_rate\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"5\" name=\"fmt\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Feed app (&quot;internal&quot;) audio to the running stream (the mic, if enabled in [code]stream_start[/code], is captured natively). [code]samples[/code] is raw PCM; [code]fmt[/code] 0 = s16 / 8 = float. Source it from an [code]AudioEffectCapture[/code] on the master bus. Returns the encoder status ([code]-1[/code] if not streaming).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"stream_push_frame\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"gl_texture_id\" type=\"int\" /><param index=\"1\" name=\"timestamp_ns\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Feed one frame to the running stream: [code]gl_texture_id[/code] from [code]RenderingServer.texture_get_native_handle[/code] on the view&#39;s texture, [code]timestamp_ns[/code] in nanoseconds. [b]Call inside a [code]RenderingServer.call_on_render_thread[/code] callback[/b] (the encoder reads the GL texture on the render thread&#39;s EGL context). Returns the encoder status ([code]0[/code] ok, [code]-1[/code] if not streaming).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"stream_stop\">\n"
"  <return type=\"void\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Stop + tear down the FPV stream.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"is_stream_active\">\n"
"  <return type=\"bool\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Whether an FPV stream is currently active.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_stereo_mode\">\n"
"  <return type=\"void\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"mode\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Select the stereo rendering mode applied when the native session [b]bootstraps[/b] (a startup selector): [code]0[/code] = Multipass (both eyes — the default shipping path), [code]2[/code] = Multiview (single-pass-instanced). [b]Call before the session starts[/b] (e.g. an autoload [code]_ready[/code], before the XR rig enters the tree) — it is read once at [code]InitUserDefinedSettings[/code]. Equivalent to the ProjectSetting [code]xreal/stereo_mode[/code] or [code]adb shell setprop debug.xreal.stereo_mode &lt;n&gt;[/code]. Multiview buys nothing on this two-SubViewport rig (see docs/archive/multiview-investigation.md), so Multipass stays the recommended default.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"set_tracking_type\">\n"
"  <return type=\"void\" />\n"
"  <param index=\"0\" name=\"mode\" type=\"int\" />\n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Select the head-tracking mode applied when the native session [b]bootstraps[/b] (a startup selector): [code]0[/code] = 6DoF (SLAM position + orientation, no drift — the recommended mode), [code]1[/code] = 3DoF (IMU orientation only, no position), [code]2[/code] = 0DoF. [b]Call before the session starts[/b] (e.g. an autoload [code]_ready[/code], before the XR rig enters the tree) — it is read once at [code]InitUserDefinedSettings[/code]. Equivalent to the ProjectSetting [code]xreal/tracking_type[/code] or [code]adb shell setprop debug.xreal.tracking_type &lt;n&gt;[/code]. Use [code]get_tracking_type()[/code] for the mode actually active on the running session, and [code]switch_tracking_type()[/code] to change it at runtime (SDK call; may be unavailable mid-session).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_hmd_time_nanos\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Current HMD clock in nanoseconds ([code]0[/code] while the perception pipe is down).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_diagnostics\">\n"
"  <return type=\"String\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  One-line diagnostic of the perception pipeline (session/clock/pose state).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_present_fps\">\n"
"  <return type=\"float\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Present rate in frames/second (compositor, integer ~60). [code]-1.0[/code] while the metrics handle is not up yet.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_dropped_frame_count\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Frames dropped by the compositor. [code]-1[/code] while the metrics handle is not up yet.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_early_frame_count\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Frames presented early. [code]-1[/code] while the metrics handle is not up yet.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_frame_present_count\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Present count for the current frame (FPC). [code]-1[/code] while the metrics handle is not up yet.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_extended_frame_count\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Extended (re-projected/stale) frame count (EFC). [code]-1[/code] while the metrics handle is not up yet.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_teared_frame_count\">\n"
"  <return type=\"int\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Teared frame count. [code]-1[/code] when unavailable (also the SDK&#39;s own &quot;not tracked&quot; sentinel).\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_frame_composite_time_ms\">\n"
"  <return type=\"float\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  Compositor frame composite time in milliseconds. [code]-1.0[/code] while the metrics handle is not up yet.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_app_frame_latency_ms\">\n"
"  <return type=\"float\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  App frame latency (motion-to-photon input) in milliseconds. [code]-1.0[/code] while unavailable.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"\n"
"<method name=\"get_render_metrics_diagnostics\">\n"
"  <return type=\"String\" />\n"
"  \n"
"  <description>\n"
"  One-line diagnostic / start status of the render-metrics handle.\n"
"  </description>\n"
"</method>\n"
"</methods>\n"
"<constants><constant name=\"TRACKING_6DOF\" value=\"0\">[code]TrackingType[/code] for [code]switch_tracking_type[/code] / [code]get_tracking_type[/code] (from the Unity [code]XREALPlugin.cs[/code] enum): 6DoF — SLAM position + orientation (the recommended mode).</constant><constant name=\"TRACKING_3DOF\" value=\"1\">[code]TrackingType[/code]: 3DoF — IMU orientation only, no position.</constant><constant name=\"TRACKING_0DOF\" value=\"2\">[code]TrackingType[/code]: 0DoF — no head tracking.</constant><constant name=\"TRACKING_0DOF_STAB\" value=\"3\">[code]TrackingType[/code]: 0DoF with stabilization.</constant><constant name=\"FEATURE_RGB_CAMERA\" value=\"1\">[code]XREALSupportedFeature[/code] for [[code]Self::is_hmd_feature_supported[/code]]: the RGB camera.</constant><constant name=\"FEATURE_WEARING_STATUS\" value=\"2\">[code]XREALSupportedFeature[/code]: the proximity (wear) sensor.</constant><constant name=\"FEATURE_CONTROLLER\" value=\"3\">[code]XREALSupportedFeature[/code]: a handheld controller.</constant><constant name=\"FEATURE_HEAD_TRACKING_ROTATION\" value=\"4\">[code]XREALSupportedFeature[/code]: head-tracking rotation (3DoF).</constant><constant name=\"FEATURE_HEAD_TRACKING_POSITION\" value=\"5\">[code]XREALSupportedFeature[/code]: head-tracking position (6DoF).</constant><constant name=\"COMPONENT_RGB_CAMERA\" value=\"crate::ffi::component::RGB_CAMERA\">[code]XREALComponent[/code] id for the geometry getters: the RGB camera.</constant><constant name=\"COMPONENT_DISPLAY_LEFT\" value=\"crate::ffi::component::DISPLAY_LEFT\">[code]XREALComponent[/code] id: the left display.</constant><constant name=\"COMPONENT_DISPLAY_RIGHT\" value=\"crate::ffi::component::DISPLAY_RIGHT\">[code]XREALComponent[/code] id: the right display.</constant><constant name=\"COMPONENT_GRAYSCALE_LEFT\" value=\"crate::ffi::component::GRAYSCALE_CAMERA_LEFT\">[code]XREALComponent[/code] id: the left SLAM grayscale camera.</constant><constant name=\"COMPONENT_GRAYSCALE_RIGHT\" value=\"crate::ffi::component::GRAYSCALE_CAMERA_RIGHT\">[code]XREALComponent[/code] id: the right SLAM grayscale camera.</constant><constant name=\"PLANE_NONE\" value=\"0\">[code]PlaneDetectionMode[/code] flag for [[code]Self::set_plane_detection_mode[/code]] / [[code]Self::poll_planes[/code]]: detection off.</constant><constant name=\"PLANE_HORIZONTAL\" value=\"1\">[code]PlaneDetectionMode[/code] flag: detect horizontal planes (floors, tables).</constant><constant name=\"PLANE_VERTICAL\" value=\"2\">[code]PlaneDetectionMode[/code] flag: detect vertical planes (walls).</constant><constant name=\"PLANE_BOTH\" value=\"3\">[code]PlaneDetectionMode[/code] flag: detect both horizontal and vertical planes.</constant><constant name=\"ANCHOR_QUALITY_INSUFFICIENT\" value=\"0\">Anchor-quality level from [[code]Self::estimate_anchor_quality[/code]]: insufficient — do not save here.</constant><constant name=\"ANCHOR_QUALITY_SUFFICIENT\" value=\"1\">Anchor-quality level: sufficient — the minimum recommended before saving.</constant><constant name=\"ANCHOR_QUALITY_GOOD\" value=\"2\">Anchor-quality level: good — a strong spot to save an anchor.</constant></constants>\n"
"\n"
"<members></members>\n"
"</class>\n"
,
};
enum { STUB_DOC_COUNT = sizeof(stub_docs) / sizeof(stub_docs[0]) };
